---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LeadForm from '@/components/LeadForm.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Relocating to Asheville &amp; WNC"
  description="A working guide to relocating to Asheville and Western North Carolina — choosing your community, visiting the area, and the logistics most people don't think about until they're knee-deep."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-sun-600">Relocating</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 font-display text-4xl text-mountain-900 sm:text-5xl">
      Move here once. Move here right.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-lg text-mountain-600">
      Most relocators land in Asheville, fall in love over a long weekend, and then
      immediately discover the area is bigger and more textured than the postcards.
      My job is to help you make a decision that holds up at year five — not just at month one.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-mountain-900">Step 1 — figure out which corner of WNC fits you</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-mountain-700">
        Asheville is the gravity center, but Black Mountain, Weaverville, Hendersonville,
        Brevard, Fairview, and a dozen smaller places each pull a different kind of buyer.
        We'll talk through what your weeks look like, then narrow the map.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-mountain-700">
        <strong>Coming soon:</strong> the
        <a href="/where-should-you-live/">Where should you live in WNC?</a> matcher —
        a short, lifestyle-driven quiz that recommends two or three areas based on lot size,
        commute, outdoor priorities, and price.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-mountain-900">Step 2 — visit the area on purpose</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-mountain-700">
        Most folks visit Asheville like tourists. As your Realtor I'll structure a
        visit that lets you see it like a future resident — neighborhoods you're
        considering, drive-times in real traffic, the schools and grocery stores
        and trailheads you'd actually use, plus the hidden corners you can't find on Google.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl text-mountain-900">Step 3 — handle the logistics</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-mountain-700">
        Closing dates that align with school calendars. Movers booked. Contractors
        scheduled for the things you want done before you arrive. Lender lined up.
        Septic, well, HOA, insurance — the WNC-specific gotchas that catch coastal
        and city buyers off-guard. This is where I earn it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <LeadForm
        source="relocate-bottom"
        heading="Thinking about the move?"
        blurb="Tell me where you're moving from, what your timeline looks like, and what your week needs to feel like. I'll come back with thoughts on a few areas to consider."
      />
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
